ad.title: Experienced and Engaging Australian Nanny
ad.content: I'm a cheerful and energetic Australian with a long history of working with children of a variety of ages and needs. Now living in France on a working holiday visa with my husband, I'm excited to find a role where I can bring my love of caring for and teaching kids to life! Before moving to France, I worked as a social worker supporting parents. Previously, I spent over 10 years as a babysitter and 6 years as a part-time nanny for four families, caring for children from newborns to teenagers. My experience includes working with children from diverse backgrounds, those who speak languages other than English, and children with additional needs, including immunocompromised toddlers. While completing my studies, I worked in the community service sector as a Case Worker focusing on youth services and disability, and as a student support worker at an education support high school for teenagers with disabilities. Before that, I spent five years as a Youth Worker while also providing casual childcare and nannying services, including short-term care for families. I excel at engaging with children of all ages, from entertaining lively toddlers to assisting with homework, activities, and supporting those with learning challenges. I can prepare meals and perform light housekeeping. My passion for the wellbeing of children and young people drives my dedication to providing excellent care. Currently I only speak basic French but I am starting an intensive course very soon.
